Paper: hep-th/9801080

Date: 1998-01-13

Title: Some Aspects of N=(2,2), D=2 Supersymmetry

Authors: M.T. Grisaru, M. Massar, A. Sevrin, J. Troost

Comments: 6 pages, Latex, to appear in the proceedings of `Quantum aspects of

gauge theories, supersymmetry and unification', Neuchatel University, 18-23September 1997Journal-ref: Fortsch.Phys. 47 (1999) 301-307

The off-shell description of N=(2,2) supersymmetric non-linear sigma-modelsis reviewed. The conditions for ultra-violet finiteness are derived andT-duality is discussed in detail.